programme.desc: Antiques dealers Ian Humphries, Harry Khwaja and Jo Roberts head to L'Isle-sur-la-Sorgue, which boasts a picture-perfect market set against a backdrop of canals and waterwheels due to its historical links to the wool trade. There they compete to find two hidden treasures each, to buy and sell online for the most profit. The trio's first challenge is to find something they know will appeal to their loyal customers and social media followers, but time isn't on their side

programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are? USA: Laverne Cox
programme.desc: Actress and activist Laverne Cox pieces together the inspiring life of her African-American ancestor who challenged societal norms and pushed the boundaries, just years after emancipation

programme.title: Scotland from the Sky
programme.desc: James Crawford explores the ways that the Scottish people have managed to surmount the challenges of tough terrain to connect communities and places across the centuries. Taking to the air in a seaplane, he visits Loch Ness to reveal its geological secrets, uncovers traces of the Viking era, explores how we have crossed the treacherous Pentland Firth and flies above the stunning West Highland line. Finally, he visits the Highland crofters and Scotland's first spaceport

programme.title: Flog It!: Derbyshire 8
programme.desc: Antiques experts Michael Baggott and Caroline Hawley inspect an oriental carving and a model of a Second World War V1 bomb brought in by members of the public looking to make a sale at Derbyshire's Haddon Hall. Plus, presenter Paul Martin explores the history of the Peak District National Park

programme.title: Richard Osman's House of Games: Week 14 - Thursday
programme.desc: Tasha Ghouri, Jon Kay, Alexandra Mardell and Griff Rhys Jones take part in the penultimate round of challenges ahead of Friday's final

programme.title: Clive Myrie's African Adventure
programme.desc: Clive arrives in Ghana, and his first stop is the beachside capital of Accra. He heads to one of the world's biggest second-hand markets to meet the designers giving discarded clothes another chance. Once kitted out with a new look, Clive heads to the studio of Dancegod Lloyd to learn moves from the man who turned traditional dance moves into viral hits, and who starred in a Beyonce video

programme.title: Celebrity Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Newscaster Nina Hossain and fellow reporter Lucrezia Millarini drive a custard-coloured 1955 Ford Pop Hot Rod, with expert advice provided by Tim Medhurst and Steven Moore, who are piloting a 1960s Ford Thames between the antique shops and emporia. Their shopping bonanza between Nottinghamshire and Derbyshire will end at an auction in Buckinghamshire

programme.title: Your Home Made Perfect: Hemal and Kapila
programme.desc: Hemal and Kapila have wrestled with how to improve their four-bedroom family home and make the space work better for them and their three children, but their ideas for a project have not moved forward. Now, architects Will Foster and Lizzie Fraher compete using virtual reality to win the opportunity to remodel the property. Presented by Angela Scanlon

programme.title: Cold Case Investigators: Solving Britain's Sex Crimes
programme.desc: Part two of two. Modern DNA testing helps detectives find a rapist who posed as a cab driver and has gone unpunished for nearly 30 years. Investigators reveal their findings on the identity of the man who kidnapped and sexually assaulted two schoolgirls in 2002

programme.title: Grand Tours of Scotland's Lochs: The Wild Way of the North
programme.sub-title: The Wild Way of the North Season 3, Episode 1
programme.desc: Paul Murton returns to explore more of the nation's lochs, beginning by heading to Wester Ross to find out about the heritage of Little Loch Broom. He then travels to the off-grid community of Scoraig, where he learns about violin making and wind power, before taking the plunge to explore the hidden depths of Corrieshalloch Gorge. In Ullapool, on the shores of Loch Broom, Paul learns the Russian word for parsley, and how a huge fleet of Russian fish factory ships known as Klondykers used to visit the town

programme.title: The Apprentice: Unfinished Business: Hong Kong
programme.desc: As Alan Sugar launches his latest search for a new business partner, Angela Scanlon and her guests take a deep dive into the candidates' performances and analyse the task, the boardrooms and the firings. Plus, a chat with the first person to leave the process

programme.title: Newsnight: 29/01/2026
programme.desc: Analysis of the day's events with Paddy O'Connell

programme.title: Weather: 29/01/2026
programme.desc: The latest forecast

programme.title: Mystery Road: Origin
programme.desc: Jay's rough justice gets an unexpected response. One disappearance is resolved, but the other's outcome proves aggravating. Drama, starring Mark Coles Smith

programme.title: Nature's Fight Club
programme.desc: Een programma over de overlevingsstrijd van dieren. Ze moeten zich elke dag opnieuw zorgen maken over hun veiligheid, territoria en voedselbronnen en moeten zich verdedigen tegen andere soortgenoten. Elk gevecht gaat over leven en dood.

programme.title: Nature's Fight Club

programme.desc: Er wordt ingegaan op het belang van partnerkeuze voor de voortplanting van levende wezens en het voortbestaan van hun soort. Het is niet ongewoon dat er een gevecht plaatsvindt waarbij alleen de winnaar erin slaagt het vrouwtje te bevruchten.

programme.desc: Als je over de planeet naar het noorden reist, zul je uiteindelijk geen bos meer hebben, en een grond treffen dat te hard is voor bomen om zich te wortelen. Dit is toendra. Maar het gebied biedt rijke beloningen voor degenen die sterk genoeg zijn.

programme.title: Wonderful Wetlands
